WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:16.320 --> 02:18.277
Hang in there, Sergeant.

02:22.040 --> 02:24.919
American heroism has a new face today.

02:25.080 --> 02:27.037
Despite heavy enemy fire,

02:27.120 --> 02:30.909
a young infantryman rushes to the aid
of his fallen sergeant.

02:31.000 --> 02:33.435
This now-famous image
was captured on a camera

02:33.520 --> 02:35.637
abandoned by an embedded reporter

02:35.800 --> 02:41.159
during an ambush by anti-coalition forces
in Al-Ansakar, Diyala Province, Iraq.

02:41.360 --> 02:45.673
Nineteen-year-old Specialist William Lynn
was awarded the Silver Star,

02:45.800 --> 02:47.917
and he and the eight-man Bravo squad

02:48.080 --> 02:50.754
have spent the last two weeks
touring the country,

02:50.840 --> 02:52.832
receiving the nation's thanks.

02:52.920 --> 02:56.630
Their tour ends right here in Dallas,
where they'll be performing

02:56.760 --> 02:59.992
in Thursday's halftime show
alongside Destiny's Child.

03:13.160 --> 03:14.435
Hello?

03:14.560 --> 03:16.517
Hey, Billy. How's your head, buddy?

03:16.640 --> 03:18.518
- What?
- You get a good night's sleep?

03:18.600 --> 03:21.479
Yeah, those strippers last night
were really into you, man.

03:21.560 --> 03:23.199
What are you talking about?

03:23.280 --> 03:24.839
Hey, remember that halftime show
we're doing?

03:24.920 --> 03:26.320
- Shit!
- With Destiny's Child?

03:26.400 --> 03:27.720
Why don't you join us, dumbass?

03:27.800 --> 03:29.996
Here's the reason why people love this story.

03:30.120 --> 03:32.919
They give us hope,
they give us reason not to despair.

03:33.560 --> 03:34.630
Yeah.

03:34.720 --> 03:36.757
Six minutes and 40 seconds late.

03:36.840 --> 03:37.910
Yes.

03:38.200 --> 03:41.238
- Are you flakin' on me, Lynn?
- No, Sergeant.

03:41.320 --> 03:43.152
Just dreaming about cheerleaders.

03:43.360 --> 03:45.113
- Good man.
- I know it's not a popular war,

03:45.200 --> 03:47.271
and I know what's going on
in the media right now,

03:47.360 --> 03:49.875
but Bravo's a story about America
feeling good about America again.

03:50.000 --> 03:52.640
When the last time you felt good
about that, huh? Tell me.

03:53.080 --> 03:55.959
Dude! She really liked me.
She gave me a freebie.

03:56.160 --> 03:59.039
Sykes, you are so full of shit, man.
We were all wasted last night.

03:59.120 --> 04:01.635
I can't remember shit.
You sure as hell can't remember shit.

04:01.760 --> 04:03.558
Well, all I know is I got a free dance.

04:03.680 --> 04:06.798
We all got a free dance, boy.
Strippers love their country, too.

04:06.880 --> 04:08.075
What I'm saying is,

04:08.160 --> 04:10.277
there was a connection between us,
you know?

04:10.360 --> 04:11.476
Emotion and shit.

04:11.560 --> 04:15.110
That's her job, motherfucker.
Supposed to make you feel like they like you.

04:15.200 --> 04:17.077
Waitress, actress, stripper, prostitute.

04:17.160 --> 04:18.640
Go fuck yourself.

04:18.720 --> 04:20.358
Come on. At ease with the trash talk, fellas.

04:20.440 --> 04:23.080
- We're in front of civilians.
- Yeah. Hey, listen up, all of you.

04:23.200 --> 04:25.271
Right now,
by the grace of God and the media,

04:25.360 --> 04:27.352
we are the face of the American military,

04:27.440 --> 04:29.796
and you will act accordingly.
Do I make myself clear?

04:29.880 --> 04:31.030
Hooah!

04:31.360 --> 04:32.794
Man, we're gonna look ridiculous.

04:32.880 --> 04:34.837
Tell me about it, man. This whole tour's been

04:34.960 --> 04:36.713
one big dog-and-pony show
for the cameras, Sergeant.

04:36.800 --> 04:38.314
Those were just local appearances.

04:38.400 --> 04:41.040
At halftime, we will be performing
on national television

04:41.120 --> 04:42.952
in front of 40 million viewers.

04:43.040 --> 04:45.794
Now, if that happens to be
the mother of all clusterfucks,

04:45.880 --> 04:47.678
then we should blame it on bad intelligence.

04:47.760 --> 04:48.750
Inspiring words, Sergeant.

04:48.840 --> 04:50.638
No, they're not the...
No, they're not the elite force.

04:50.720 --> 04:53.955
No, they're a bunch of kids thrown into
the deep end of a not-so-popular war.

04:54.040 --> 04:55.110
And what do they do?

04:55.200 --> 04:57.476
They bond together with love
and brotherhood, that's what they do.

04:57.560 --> 04:59.597
You can't write that shit, man. Come on!

05:01.560 --> 05:02.880
You guys the Bravos?

05:03.360 --> 05:04.510
What gave us away?

05:06.080 --> 05:07.639
Sergeant David Dime.

05:07.880 --> 05:11.794
These are the men of 2nd Squad,
otherwise known to the media as "Bravo."

05:11.880 --> 05:14.156
Well, I'm Josh. I'm liaison from the team,

05:14.240 --> 05:16.197
so if you guys need anything today,
you just tell me.

05:16.280 --> 05:17.953
- I'll be taking care of you, all right?
- Hooah.

05:18.040 --> 05:19.679
Sykes would like his dignity back.

05:19.760 --> 05:21.513
- Crack needs to go fuck himself.
- Come on.

05:21.600 --> 05:24.069
This is Albert Brown,
producer extraordinaire.

05:24.280 --> 05:25.999
- How are you?
- Army set us up with him.

05:26.080 --> 05:27.992
You ever seen the "Fight Night" movies?

05:28.400 --> 05:30.312
- No.
- Well, you're missing out.

05:31.720 --> 05:33.552
He'll be rolling with us today.

05:34.040 --> 05:35.110
Is everybody here?

05:35.200 --> 05:37.476
- Present and accounted for.
- Wait, where's Major Mac?

05:37.560 --> 05:38.994
We're missing our public affairs coordinator.

05:39.080 --> 05:40.150
He's here, Sergeant.

05:40.640 --> 05:42.836
Major McLaurin, I'm Josh.
I'm gonna be taking care of you...

05:42.920 --> 05:43.910
He can't hear you.

05:44.000 --> 05:46.515
Major McLaurin was blown up
on the first day of his tour

05:46.600 --> 05:48.910
by an improvised explosive device.

05:49.200 --> 05:51.112
Twice. Lost his hearing.

05:52.120 --> 05:55.238
I'm... I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

05:55.440 --> 05:58.035
Well, here's your ride to the stadium.

05:58.120 --> 06:00.589
Courtesy of Mr. Oglesby.
So if you guys'll just...

06:01.040 --> 06:03.680
Wait, wait. Norm Oglesby sent this?

06:03.800 --> 06:05.792
Who the fuck is Norm Oglesby?

06:11.280 --> 06:13.351
All right, now,
that's what I'm talkin' about.

06:13.440 --> 06:15.079
- Just one little drink, Sergeant.
- No!

06:15.160 --> 06:16.196
But, Sergeant...

06:16.280 --> 06:19.159
Sykes, have you not had
your morning glass of shut-up?

06:27.480 --> 06:30.871
"Quietness, quietness over this countryside,

06:31.520 --> 06:34.194
"except for unmistakable signals on radio...

06:35.440 --> 06:37.591
"Has anyone looked in the eyes of the dead?

06:39.040 --> 06:42.431
"Is anyone living
to look for future forgiveness?"

06:47.400 --> 06:51.314
Well, I'm not much for poetry,
but this was one of Sergeant Breem...

06:51.400 --> 06:52.959
Shroom's favorites.

06:53.760 --> 06:56.070
I remember him
walking around base camp perimeter

06:56.160 --> 06:58.277
reciting this kind of stuff really loud.

06:59.040 --> 07:01.191
"Just sharing the wisdom," he said,

07:01.280 --> 07:03.476
when I'd tell him to shut the hell up.

07:04.600 --> 07:06.876
Maybe Shroom had a point.

07:08.000 --> 07:10.390
But personally, I believe
he was really using his voice

07:10.480 --> 07:13.120
to let the insurgents draw a bead on us
with their mortars,

07:13.200 --> 07:15.476
because that's the kind
of person Shroom was,

07:15.560 --> 07:17.552
always thinking of the other guy.

07:20.000 --> 07:21.559
Private Beckwith!

07:22.000 --> 07:23.116
Here, Sergeant!

07:23.200 --> 07:24.395
Sergeant Holliday!

07:24.640 --> 07:25.835
Here, Sergeant!

07:25.960 --> 07:27.235
Specialist Koch!

07:27.560 --> 07:28.960
Here, Sergeant!

07:29.280 --> 07:30.760
Specialist Yang!

07:30.840 --> 07:32.035
Here, Sergeant!

07:32.120 --> 07:33.349
Specialist Lynn!

07:33.520 --> 07:34.636
Here, Sergeant!

07:34.760 --> 07:35.750
Private Sykes!

07:35.880 --> 07:36.950
Here, Sergeant!

07:37.080 --> 07:38.639
Specialist Montoya!

07:38.840 --> 07:40.115
Here, Sergeant!

07:40.200 --> 07:42.032
Staff Sergeant Breem!

07:46.720 --> 07:48.712
Staff Sergeant Virgil Breem!

07:53.640 --> 07:56.633
Staff Sergeant Virgil Jeremiah Breem!

08:00.080 --> 08:02.117
Honor Guard! Attention!

08:04.120 --> 08:06.351
Ready! Aim!

08:06.880 --> 08:08.030
Fire!

08:08.920 --> 08:12.231
Ready! Aim! Fire!

08:24.320 --> 08:27.631
Aunt Marie said she hardly recognized you
on TV, you'd gotten so big.

08:27.720 --> 08:29.632
What's the Army been feedin' you?

08:29.720 --> 08:31.473
We order Domino's, mostly.

08:31.560 --> 08:32.676
It's easier than cooking.

08:32.760 --> 08:35.355
They don't really have those
over there, do they?

08:35.440 --> 08:38.717
Yeah. And free extra cheese
with every medal, right, Billy?

08:39.120 --> 08:40.315
Kathryn!

08:40.400 --> 08:42.517
Everyone in town's been asking about you.

08:43.080 --> 08:44.673
It's like we're celebrities.

08:45.000 --> 08:48.437
The neighbors all say how proud they are
of you and how grateful they are.

08:48.600 --> 08:51.957
Billy, you're not on duty, you're home,
so go put your dogs up.

08:52.040 --> 08:53.269
Yes, ma'am.

08:53.360 --> 08:55.352
Come help me get the casserole dish down.

08:55.440 --> 08:58.239
I'm makin' your favorite, chicken tetrazzini.

08:58.320 --> 09:00.232
Except I'm making it with turkey
instead of chicken

09:00.320 --> 09:01.834
since you can't be here for Thanksgiving.

09:01.920 --> 09:04.879
- I figure turkey's just as good, right?
- Turkey's just as good, Mom.

09:04.960 --> 09:08.840
And I have stocked the fridge
full of Cokes, Dr Pepper,

09:08.920 --> 09:11.116
sweet tea, all your favorites.

09:13.480 --> 09:15.870
Or we could slip out the back
and have a beer.

09:15.960 --> 09:17.155
Kathryn.

09:17.560 --> 09:20.519
Kathryn! Get in here and let your brother be!

09:20.640 --> 09:22.199
Change, though.

09:22.480 --> 09:25.040
You wear that to dinner,
and I'm gonna wear my prom dress.

09:25.120 --> 09:26.713
It's tempting.

09:30.160 --> 09:32.152
Hey, you, little man. What's up?

09:32.600 --> 09:35.035
You getting big and strong like your dad?

09:36.200 --> 09:37.475
Where's Pete?

09:37.560 --> 09:40.439
He's working a double shift.
He sends his regards.

09:41.400 --> 09:43.039
Billy.

09:43.200 --> 09:45.237
We've been praying for you, you know that?

09:46.480 --> 09:48.437
We're all so proud of you.

09:49.080 --> 09:50.719
...saw an opportunity and came here...

09:50.800 --> 09:53.031
- Him, too.
- ...overrunning the town and setting up

09:53.160 --> 09:55.117
- headquarters at the police station.
- In his way.

09:55.520 --> 09:57.989
Before dawn on Saturday,
Captain Brown's men,

09:58.120 --> 10:00.589
together with Iraqi forces,
some wearing masks,

10:00.720 --> 10:03.360
led an assault on the police station.

10:03.480 --> 10:04.436
Dad.

10:04.520 --> 10:08.070
After searching 24 hours,
the troops found nothing but a few guns.

10:09.240 --> 10:11.357
Locals say the insurgents
had already moved on.

10:11.520 --> 10:13.034
No drink on game day?

10:13.120 --> 10:16.591
No. No, Dan, I'm excited, too.
Yes, I'm excited. Yes.

10:16.720 --> 10:19.474
Talk to your client. I'll do my thing.
Okay. Thanks. Bye.

10:19.560 --> 10:20.880
Hey, guys. Good news. Hey.

10:20.960 --> 10:22.440
- We got interest...
- Hey, listen up.

10:22.520 --> 10:24.477
Hey, we got interest from a major star.

10:24.600 --> 10:25.954
Matt Damon?

10:26.040 --> 10:27.315
- No.
- DiCaprio.

10:27.400 --> 10:28.720
- No.
- Matt Damon?

10:28.800 --> 10:30.154
I just said, "Matt Damon".

10:30.640 --> 10:32.518
Hey. Hey, this may not be a name

10:32.640 --> 10:35.075
that comes readily to mind
to you guys, but hear me out.

10:35.160 --> 10:36.355
- Hear me out.
- All right.

10:36.440 --> 10:37.590
Hilary Swank.

10:37.680 --> 10:39.080
- Whoa.
- What?

10:39.200 --> 10:41.590
She won an Oscar playing a guy
in Boys Don't Cry.

10:41.680 --> 10:43.433
Well, she played a girl
pretending to be a guy.

10:43.520 --> 10:46.638
We know who she is. Who she is.
Why is she interested in us?

10:46.720 --> 10:48.359
Because she wants to play him.

10:50.600 --> 10:52.273
Oh, man!

10:55.840 --> 10:57.797
I know this may not be the ideal choice,

10:57.880 --> 10:59.633
but let me tell you something,
if she gets attached,

10:59.760 --> 11:02.992
other stars hear about it
and they start sniffing around,

11:03.080 --> 11:05.072
and next thing you know, Mark Wahlberg.

11:05.160 --> 11:07.117
- Dirk Diggler. Hell, yeah.
- Yeah.

11:07.200 --> 11:09.920
So, wait, wait, wait, wait.
Is she playing him as a girl,

11:10.000 --> 11:11.514
or as a girl playing a guy?

11:13.280 --> 11:16.318
If Hilary Swank gets on board,
this movie gets made.

11:16.440 --> 11:19.160
- Which means you guys get paid.
- Yeah, how much?

11:19.280 --> 11:21.636
Well, if we get a major star
and I'm just guessing,

11:21.720 --> 11:24.394
so don't hold me to it,
maybe 100 grand each.

11:24.480 --> 11:26.711
Fuck you. We could make that much?

11:26.840 --> 11:30.231
Means I got a lot of work getting it made,
and then everybody get paid,

11:30.360 --> 11:32.238
but a lot of things got to happen.

11:32.360 --> 11:34.079
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey! Boys!

11:34.160 --> 11:35.719
Hundred grand's a lot of money.

11:35.840 --> 11:37.672
Sensible ideas on how to spend it?

11:38.520 --> 11:41.877
I don't know. Probably help pay down
my sister's medical bills.

11:41.960 --> 11:43.189
Oh, yeah. Word up, yo.

11:43.280 --> 11:45.192
That's true. Family comes first, man.

11:45.280 --> 11:47.715
Like I told my moms,
I'm gonna buy her a new car.

11:47.800 --> 11:49.598
- Fuck family.
- Yeah.

11:49.680 --> 11:52.195
I'm getting myself
a top-of-the-line Sauer 202,

11:52.280 --> 11:53.919
couple of vintage fly rods,

11:54.000 --> 11:57.311
spend the next three years up in Montana
just huntin' and fishin'.

11:58.520 --> 12:00.159
Hey, what the fuck, Sykes!

12:00.280 --> 12:02.636
- Get him down now.
- Sit down, boy! Park that...

12:04.400 --> 12:06.551
Hey, hey, hey, everything okay back there?

12:06.640 --> 12:07.869
- It's all good, man.
- Yeah.

12:07.960 --> 12:09.838
- Yeah, we're good.
- Hey, Josh. Nice hair.

12:09.920 --> 12:12.071
Yeah, man, you're looking
all spiffy and crewed up.

12:12.160 --> 12:13.355
Who's your stylist, Papi?

12:13.440 --> 12:15.716
Hey, Josh, what can you tell us
about the halftime, bro?

12:15.800 --> 12:17.917
Yeah, when can I get
my lap dance from Beyoncé?

12:18.000 --> 12:19.434
- Sykes, shut!
- Hey, Josh,

12:19.520 --> 12:22.160
- do you know Norm, like, personally?
- You're full of shit, yo.

12:22.240 --> 12:24.357
For God's sake. I'm just trying to find out,

12:24.480 --> 12:26.312
Josh, what's expected of us, bro.

12:26.480 --> 12:28.073
Okay, well, there's no details yet,

12:28.160 --> 12:31.710
but knowing Mr. Oglesby,
it's sure to be a real extravaganza.

12:32.160 --> 12:33.913
Does this Hummer come with Advil?

12:34.000 --> 12:35.753
No, I don't think so. I'm sorry. But...

12:35.840 --> 12:38.196
But I'll be sure you get some
when we arrive, okay?

12:38.280 --> 12:40.954
A musical? Are you shittin' me? Larry...

12:43.000 --> 12:44.992
Billy, what if you don't go back?

12:45.960 --> 12:48.600
There are a ton of ways
you could get shipped home.

12:48.680 --> 12:50.558
Or at least out of active duty.

12:50.840 --> 12:54.390
I mean, you're a decorated hero, Billy.
You've done your part.

12:54.520 --> 12:56.477
...about more than just blowing shit up.

12:56.560 --> 12:58.916
Larry, Larry, my boys ship out in two days,

12:59.000 --> 13:01.356
and access becomes
extremely problematic after that,

13:01.440 --> 13:04.000
unless your lawyers
want to parachute into a war zone.

13:04.480 --> 13:06.790
Well, come on, let's get this shit done.

13:11.840 --> 13:13.559
Sarge, you want to stop here?

13:52.440 --> 13:53.556
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

14:02.920 --> 14:03.910
Good.

14:28.120 --> 14:29.998
Let me guess. Just fell off a truck?

14:33.720 --> 14:35.757
Says a boy brought it,
but doesn't know from where.

14:44.240 --> 14:45.390
Mister! Mister!

14:45.880 --> 14:47.712
Hello, my friend. You want big movie?

14:47.800 --> 14:49.075
Which one you got here?

14:49.200 --> 14:50.759
You want big movie? Mister!

14:50.840 --> 14:51.876
Mister! Hello!

14:51.960 --> 14:53.679
Hey, Crack, they got Finding Nemo.

14:53.760 --> 14:55.274
- I love this shit.
- Finding Nemo.

14:55.360 --> 14:56.874
- How much?
- Sykes!

14:58.480 --> 15:00.392
Aren't you a little old for that, soldier?

15:00.520 --> 15:02.716
No, Sarge, it's for... It's for my daughter.

15:10.000 --> 15:12.117
Life during wartime.

15:15.160 --> 15:16.913
Okay, guys, these are your seats right here.

15:17.000 --> 15:20.357
Got you the best row in the house.
This is Mr. Oglesby's reserved section.

15:20.480 --> 15:22.676
Make yourself at home.
You need anything, you let me know.

15:22.760 --> 15:24.479
I think... I think she likes you.

15:24.560 --> 15:26.711
- Don't you fucking lie to me.
- Hey. Stand down now,

15:26.800 --> 15:29.679
or I'll have both of you
running laps around the stadium.

15:36.400 --> 15:38.437
- Excuse me.
- Look at all these people.

15:38.760 --> 15:41.434
What do you think they're thinking about?

15:41.520 --> 15:43.273
Heavy stuff.

15:43.640 --> 15:46.394
God. Philosophy.

15:47.040 --> 15:48.633
The meaning of life.

16:01.920 --> 16:03.593
There it is.

16:05.240 --> 16:07.118
You look good.

16:08.200 --> 16:10.112
You are a shit liar.

16:10.520 --> 16:12.034
Thank you.

16:13.320 --> 16:17.314
Hey, the doctor said, and I'm quoting here,

16:17.400 --> 16:19.437
my face is 87% healed.

16:21.480 --> 16:23.153
And check it out.

16:24.560 --> 16:28.076
It's two more operations,
and that is goodbye, Miss Frankenstein.

16:29.640 --> 16:31.233
How about you?

16:31.760 --> 16:33.160
You gettin' any?

16:33.560 --> 16:34.994
None of your business.

16:35.560 --> 16:37.597
Yeah, well, that's a big fat no.

16:38.600 --> 16:40.990
So you've killed for your country
and you're still a virgin.

16:41.080 --> 16:43.640
- If that's not a sign of how fucked...
- So, how are things here?

16:43.720 --> 16:45.234
Don't change the subject.

16:45.600 --> 16:47.876
You better be out there gettin' some, boy.

16:47.960 --> 16:49.599
Are you?

16:50.200 --> 16:51.475
Guess.

16:53.920 --> 16:55.115
Some nights I'm like,

16:55.240 --> 16:58.597
whatever, maybe I'll just go
cruise the high school boys

16:58.680 --> 17:01.115
and be like,
"Hey, bubba, take a ride with me.

17:01.200 --> 17:02.680
"Once you've had a girl
with a scar on her face..."

17:02.760 --> 17:04.398
So, how are things here?

17:09.760 --> 17:11.479
I worry about you.

17:12.359 --> 17:15.159
I can't stop worrying about you.
I feel so responsible.

17:15.880 --> 17:17.030
I'm all right.

17:17.119 --> 17:19.999
Your bad.
Thanks for getting me in this shit, Kat.

17:20.640 --> 17:22.597
You know what I mean.

17:26.800 --> 17:28.200
Billy, what the fuck are you doing?

17:28.280 --> 17:29.873
Let's see what this bad boy can do.

17:29.960 --> 17:32.475
I'm not getting an Article 15 because of you.

17:32.560 --> 17:33.835
If they let us Texans all drive,

17:33.920 --> 17:36.480
there'd be no need
for PT belts and safety briefs.

17:36.560 --> 17:38.438
Just 'cause you were conceived in a truck

17:38.520 --> 17:40.477
- doesn't mean you got to die in one.
- Watch this.

17:40.560 --> 17:42.597
- Oh, shit.
- It could save your life someday.

17:43.160 --> 17:44.435
Fuck! Stop!

17:45.200 --> 17:46.793
Oh, shit!

17:47.160 --> 17:49.550
Private Lynn, you are one delinquent punk!

17:50.480 --> 17:52.073
No excuse, Sergeant.

