Actually, no, I don't.

33:56.520 --> 33:58.671
I have no idea how
those pageant deals work.

33:58.960 --> 34:01.236
I don't know much about anything, really.

34:02.120 --> 34:03.839
Could have fooled me.

34:03.920 --> 34:07.197
I've gotten kind of used to telling people
stuff they want to hear.

34:07.520 --> 34:09.637
No. You put it right out there.

34:09.840 --> 34:12.309
And that's strong. I mean...

34:13.159 --> 34:15.469
Grappling with the enemy up close like that.

34:15.679 --> 34:18.559
Your friend's death.
You were right there with him.

34:19.320 --> 34:22.472
Can't be easy talking to a roomful
of strangers about those things.

34:23.159 --> 34:26.995
It is sort of weird being honored
for the worst day of your life.

34:28.440 --> 34:30.033
It's like...

34:32.440 --> 34:33.715
Never mind.

34:36.239 --> 34:38.152
So, what's it like being a cheerleader?

34:39.360 --> 34:41.079
You really want to know?

34:41.199 --> 34:42.953
Yeah. I really do.

34:43.800 --> 34:44.870
Really.

34:45.400 --> 34:47.277
Well, it's great.

34:47.360 --> 34:50.592
I mean, people see us on TV,

34:51.000 --> 34:53.389
and they think that's all there is to it.

34:53.480 --> 34:57.076
You know, dancing and having fun,

34:57.600 --> 35:01.276
but community service
is actually the main part of our job.

35:01.400 --> 35:05.030
Visiting hospitals,
working with underprivileged kids,

35:05.200 --> 35:07.192
stuff like that, you know?

35:07.400 --> 35:10.677
To me, that's been the most satisfying thing
about being a cheerleader,

35:11.200 --> 35:14.352
serving others. The spiritual aspect of it.

35:15.160 --> 35:16.310
Billy,

35:18.320 --> 35:21.279
are you a Christian?

35:25.120 --> 35:27.157
I'm searching.

35:27.680 --> 35:29.034
Do you pray?

35:30.560 --> 35:32.711
Not as much as I should.

35:33.560 --> 35:35.517
I never got much from going to church,

35:35.600 --> 35:38.240
but then in Iraq,
in the middle of all this shooting,

35:38.400 --> 35:42.235
my friend Shroom, Sergeant Breem, gets hit.

35:42.760 --> 35:45.434
He's just, you know,

35:46.400 --> 35:48.995
lying there, bleeding out.

35:49.640 --> 35:53.395
And when I go to him, suddenly,
for the first time in my life,

35:53.560 --> 35:56.473
I feel close to something...

35:58.800 --> 36:03.352
I don't know, bigger than myself.

36:04.680 --> 36:08.993
And when Shroom died,
I felt something passing through me,

36:09.280 --> 36:10.714
like...

36:12.600 --> 36:15.069
Like his soul or...

36:16.600 --> 36:18.034
I don't know.

36:18.960 --> 36:20.076
Billy.

36:20.960 --> 36:23.236
Most of the time, that's how it works.

36:23.760 --> 36:26.958
Life gets so dark,
and we think all the light's gone out of us,

36:27.920 --> 36:29.673
but it's always there.

36:30.120 --> 36:34.558
If we just open the door a crack,
the light comes pouring in.

36:35.160 --> 36:37.755
You know how we kept looking at each...

36:38.400 --> 36:40.790
I think God wanted us to meet today.

36:41.800 --> 36:44.554
We are all called to be his lights
out in the world.

36:47.720 --> 36:50.599
And I truly believe that we...

36:51.960 --> 36:54.111
Look, if you couldn't deliver,
why'd you tell the guys that number?

36:54.200 --> 36:56.556
Now they think they're coming home
to Jacuzzis and shit.

36:56.640 --> 36:58.199
I told them a lot of things have to happen.

36:58.320 --> 37:00.516
It's Thanksgiving in LA.
I just need more time to deliver.

37:00.600 --> 37:02.319
- Yeah, we don't have time, Albert.
- I... I know.

37:03.480 --> 37:05.711
- Jesus, what happened to you?
- Nothing.

37:05.800 --> 37:07.951
Why do you look like you just got laid?

37:09.720 --> 37:12.554
Gather round, boys.
Here's a little gift for you from the team.

37:12.640 --> 37:13.630
Answers.

37:13.720 --> 37:15.791
- Thank you.
- Now, these are actual game balls.

37:16.200 --> 37:19.352
But they'll look better with a little
ink on 'em, don't you think?

37:19.640 --> 37:21.632
Hooah. Thank you.

37:21.840 --> 37:23.433
There you go.

37:24.360 --> 37:25.760
Thank you, sir.

37:27.680 --> 37:29.478
- Thanks.
- No problem.

37:29.640 --> 37:30.869
Hey, listen.

37:31.200 --> 37:33.317
What you carry out there?

37:33.520 --> 37:37.719
Most of the time my weapon's the M4,
standard semi-automatic assault rifle.

37:37.840 --> 37:41.754
A few times I've been on the.50,
what we carry on top of our Humvees.

37:41.880 --> 37:45.669
That's a heavy machine gun,
lays down 550 rounds a minute.

37:46.520 --> 37:49.240
Incendiary rounds
that could punch through an inch of steel.

37:49.560 --> 37:50.789
The M4.

37:51.440 --> 37:54.319
I mean, what does it do
when it... When it hits somebody?

37:56.200 --> 37:58.396
- Fucks 'em up.
- But does it kill them?

37:59.160 --> 38:01.629
I mean, stopping power's what I'm getting at.

38:02.200 --> 38:05.796
Maybe not with a body shot.
That's why we aim for the face.

38:06.040 --> 38:09.078
The.50, I read about that sucker
in Guns & Ammo.

38:09.240 --> 38:12.199
Been in every single war since the 1920s.
What's that one like?

38:14.000 --> 38:18.517
Well, you hit someone with a.50,
it takes 'em apart like...

38:19.480 --> 38:20.960
Like a pink mist.

38:22.200 --> 38:23.634
You ever kill somebody?

38:23.720 --> 38:25.996
I mean, like...

38:26.720 --> 38:28.279
Watch 'em die?

38:28.720 --> 38:29.870
Yes.

38:29.960 --> 38:31.758
What's that feel like?

38:32.400 --> 38:35.552
It doesn't feel like anything.
Not while it's happening.

38:35.720 --> 38:37.552
Come on, man.

38:37.720 --> 38:39.552
- You can tell us.
- Come on.

38:42.560 --> 38:47.351
What's it feel like when you hit somebody?
Like, really connect.

38:54.720 --> 38:57.519
Look at the crap they use
to protect themselves.

38:57.600 --> 38:59.671
- Do you guys have half this shit?
- Nope.

38:59.760 --> 39:02.434
Grab an equipment bag
and you can take some back.

39:02.520 --> 39:03.510
Do it.

39:03.600 --> 39:05.353
Hey, Billy, find where
they're keeping the steroids?

39:07.080 --> 39:08.275
Roy.

39:08.360 --> 39:11.956
You remember my wife, Nikki. Tiffany.
Excuse me.

39:12.400 --> 39:14.392
Hello. Thrilled you could come.

39:20.840 --> 39:22.069
Come on in.

39:23.400 --> 39:24.629
Thank you.

39:26.280 --> 39:29.398
Now, normally, I like to give
thanks to God before kickoff

39:29.480 --> 39:31.711
for the blessings we've received...

39:32.200 --> 39:33.839
And the games we've won.

39:36.280 --> 39:39.478
But this Thanksgiving,
I want to honor my special guests.

39:39.600 --> 39:41.990
A group of soldiers called Bravo.

39:43.120 --> 39:45.760
Their presence here serves as a reminder

39:45.840 --> 39:47.718
that we must not only give thanks
for our bounty,

39:47.960 --> 39:49.952
but we must also defend it.

39:50.640 --> 39:54.793
And in times of grave threat,
mount an aggressive offense

39:55.360 --> 39:59.240
if America is to hang on to that trophy
of being the greatest nation on Earth.

40:00.600 --> 40:02.000
Door left, door right!

40:02.320 --> 40:04.357
- Got door right.
- Sykes! Foo, get them up!

40:04.480 --> 40:06.312
Get up! Get up! Get the fuck up!

40:06.480 --> 40:08.039
- Hurry up!
- Come on!

40:08.800 --> 40:10.314
Don't fuckin' move!

40:10.440 --> 40:12.511
Don't fuckin' move! You stay right there.

40:12.680 --> 40:13.670
- Okay.
- You stay!

40:13.920 --> 40:15.991
- Foo, check the back.
- Got it.

40:17.960 --> 40:19.997
- All clear.
- Room clear.

40:20.320 --> 40:22.152
- Check that kitchen.
- Do you have any weapons?

40:23.800 --> 40:25.519
No. He doesn't have anything.

40:25.840 --> 40:27.593
He says to tell you there's nothing here.

40:27.680 --> 40:29.990
Are you working
with the anti-coalition forces?

40:32.800 --> 40:36.350
This is ridiculous. He is a simple man.
He's taking care of his family.

40:36.880 --> 40:37.916
He is not the enemy.

40:38.000 --> 40:40.515
Are you hiding anyone or anything?

40:42.640 --> 40:44.677
- That's crazy. He's not...
- Look at this shit.

40:44.840 --> 40:47.833
Come on. You just said you had no weapons.

40:52.200 --> 40:54.874
It is a personal gun.
For personal use to defend his family.

40:54.960 --> 40:56.679
There's no government, no law.

40:57.880 --> 40:59.872
You think I'm going to fight
the Americans with a pistol?

41:00.040 --> 41:02.032
- Hey.
- And these papers?

41:04.720 --> 41:05.949
He was a colonel in the military.

41:06.040 --> 41:08.032
These are his personal things, his memories.

41:11.960 --> 41:13.838
We got more houses to get to, Sergeant.

41:15.440 --> 41:16.760
What's he saying?

41:17.760 --> 41:18.830
Interpret!

41:18.960 --> 41:20.440
Sorry, he's upset. He's not...

41:20.560 --> 41:22.916
Hey, hey, hey, Sergeant, check this out.

41:34.800 --> 41:37.315
Enough! Enough!

41:37.760 --> 41:39.319
Zip them up and put them in the truck!

41:40.600 --> 41:42.239
Do you not fear me?

41:42.320 --> 41:44.152
I'm fuckin' serious... Get the fuck off!

41:44.240 --> 41:47.392
Easy. Easy, man. Easy.

41:48.760 --> 41:49.750
Go easy.

41:55.280 --> 41:58.000
He says he knows once you take him
he's not coming back.

42:05.440 --> 42:08.239
Tell them we're just going
to verify their identities.

42:10.160 --> 42:12.595
Then they'll be brought back to their family.

42:33.800 --> 42:36.315
So let's give 'em
a big-as-all-hell Texas welcome.

42:48.000 --> 42:49.514
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

42:50.280 --> 42:52.237
- Hey, what'll you have?
- How about an OJ?

42:52.320 --> 42:53.470
Cool.

42:53.560 --> 42:54.835
Thanks a lot, Joe.

43:01.800 --> 43:03.678
- My man.
- Hell, yeah.

43:07.120 --> 43:09.316
Hey, it's all coming together.
Just taking a little time.

43:09.520 --> 43:11.512
Now, how you gonna finance this film?

43:11.600 --> 43:13.557
We have a lot of interest in Hollywood.

43:13.640 --> 43:15.359
That's a problem, Albert.

43:15.480 --> 43:20.032
The way I see it, Bravo's here,
and Hollywood is way the heck over there.

43:20.920 --> 43:22.354
And frankly, I don't think these studio folks

43:22.440 --> 43:25.717
have the moral fortitude
to grasp the true stakes of Bravo's story.

43:25.800 --> 43:28.440
You have a point there, Norm.
You have a point.

43:28.560 --> 43:31.951
What do you mean you don't disagree?
If you agree, then buy the thing.

43:32.040 --> 43:33.235
If you disagree, then don't.

43:33.400 --> 43:35.198
Because when you're telling me
you don't disagree,

43:35.360 --> 43:37.511
what I hear is you don't have
an opinion whatsoever.

43:38.520 --> 43:41.115
Sorry, ma'am. Just keep your hands
and feet away from their mouths

43:41.200 --> 43:42.680
and you won't get hurt.

43:44.520 --> 43:46.716
That's what I'm saying,
and you keep saying the same thing.

43:46.800 --> 43:48.393
I mean, give me...

43:48.520 --> 43:50.000
So, Billy, tell us about everything.

43:50.080 --> 43:51.753
Dad, would you turn that shit off?

43:52.280 --> 43:53.316
It's loud in here.

43:53.440 --> 43:54.794
He doesn't need to be hearing
all this propaganda...

43:54.880 --> 43:55.996
Kathryn.

43:56.080 --> 43:57.560
They could cripple the economy,

43:57.720 --> 44:00.838
force widespread quarantines,
and cause sickness and death.

44:01.240 --> 44:02.594
So, how's it going?

44:05.320 --> 44:06.959
It's weird.

44:07.600 --> 44:09.796
I mean, we got rid of their dictator,

44:09.920 --> 44:12.560
and now they're fighting each other
as well as us.

44:12.720 --> 44:16.430
We're getting 'em sewer systems
and building schools,

44:16.560 --> 44:18.233
and they don't even have textbooks.

44:18.520 --> 44:21.035
We're soldiers.
What do we know about stuff like that?

44:21.760 --> 44:23.956
I'm sure y'all are doing the best you can.

44:24.920 --> 44:26.149
Yeah, with an illegal war

44:26.240 --> 44:28.436
that we should've never started
in the first place.

44:29.760 --> 44:32.639
What about all those WMDs
we keep hearing about?

44:32.760 --> 44:34.638
You see any?

44:35.160 --> 44:37.720
How about bringing democracy
to the country,

44:37.800 --> 44:40.793
- is that working out...
- Kathryn, no politics at the table.

44:40.880 --> 44:43.759
- We all know what that war is about.
- Yeah, right. The oil?

44:43.880 --> 44:46.031
Like you know everything, Kat.

44:46.280 --> 44:48.397
Like you're better
than all the people in Washington?

44:48.480 --> 44:51.234
Yeah, I think if they want a war so bad,
they should fight it themselves.

44:51.440 --> 44:54.353
It's not worth another American life,
especially not my brother's.

44:54.440 --> 44:55.669
Kathryn.

44:55.760 --> 44:57.877
- Your son.
- That's enough!

44:59.600 --> 45:00.829
What's the matter, Albert?

45:00.920 --> 45:02.195
Don't like cake?

45:02.280 --> 45:03.953
Everybody in LA is eating turkey.

45:04.440 --> 45:05.954
This is the part I hate, waiting around.

45:06.560 --> 45:08.756
Know what I do over there to kill time?

45:09.120 --> 45:10.554
I'm afraid to ask.

45:11.640 --> 45:13.279
I imagine my kid.

45:14.040 --> 45:17.795
Up here. I imagine playing with him, man.
It just levels me up.

45:19.360 --> 45:22.080
What you do over there? What's...
What's your specialty?

45:22.920 --> 45:24.240
Communications.

45:24.320 --> 45:26.596
And I'm telling you, AI, when I get out,

45:26.680 --> 45:29.673
I could be like one of them IT guys
up in some office, man.

45:29.800 --> 45:31.553
You got a skill, man.

45:32.040 --> 45:33.679
I need one of them.

45:34.240 --> 45:35.469
Hello.

45:35.640 --> 45:37.711
How has Norm been treating you fellas?

45:37.880 --> 45:41.191
Excellent, sir.
Stadium cake's just out of this world.

45:41.520 --> 45:46.595
Well, good. I just wanted to come over here
and tell you all how much I appreciate you.

45:46.760 --> 45:51.118
Oh, heck. I bet you boys have had
just about your fill of compliments by now.

45:51.440 --> 45:55.559
No. We thrive on them, sir.
It's the compliments that keep us going.

45:55.680 --> 45:58.718
You know, in the face
of the enemy's fanatical hatred.

46:00.520 --> 46:03.274
A sense of humor is a powerful weapon.

46:03.360 --> 46:05.033
My name is Wayne Pfister.

46:05.120 --> 46:08.875
Pfister Oil & Gas. 100% family-owned.

46:09.000 --> 46:13.597
We are digging deep to find
new sources of energy right here in Texas.

46:13.720 --> 46:18.920
Extracting oil out of the Barnett Shale
with a process called "hydraulic fracturing".

46:19.520 --> 46:23.480
See, some of my friends' kids
are servin' over there with y'all,

46:23.600 --> 46:28.152
so it's a personal thing for me,
lessening our dependence on foreign oil.

46:28.480 --> 46:30.836
I figure the better I do my job,

46:30.960 --> 46:33.839
the quicker we can bring
you youngsters home.

46:37.040 --> 46:38.110
Thank you, sir.

46:38.560 --> 46:40.677
We certainly do appreciate your efforts.

46:45.320 --> 46:47.039
From your own perspective,

46:47.880 --> 46:50.395
how do you think we're doing over there?

46:51.800 --> 46:53.598
How are we doing?

46:55.080 --> 46:57.072
Just from our own perspective?

46:59.800 --> 47:02.918
Well, I'm far from qualified
to speak to the big picture, sir.

47:03.080 --> 47:05.037
All I can tell you with any confidence

47:05.280 --> 47:08.956
is that the exchange of force
with intent to kill...

47:10.920 --> 47:13.833
That is truly a mind-altering
experience, sir.

47:14.080 --> 47:17.756
I can only imagine how hard it is
to face that level of violence.

47:17.920 --> 47:19.240
No.

47:19.600 --> 47:21.193
We like going lethal.

47:21.280 --> 47:23.511
I mean, isn't that
what you're paying us for, sir?

47:23.600 --> 47:26.559
Take the fight to America's enemies
and send them straight to hell?

47:26.680 --> 47:28.831
If we didn't enjoy killing people,
what'd be the point?

47:28.960 --> 47:31.759
Might as well send the Peace Corps in
to fight the war.

47:34.160 --> 47:36.595
Well, I... I guess you got me there.

47:36.760 --> 47:37.989
Sir, you see these men?

47:38.120 --> 47:40.840
I don't know how they were
before the Army got them,

47:40.960 --> 47:43.031
but you give them a weapon system
and a couple Red Bulls

47:43.120 --> 47:44.873
and they'll blast the hell
out of anything that moves.

47:44.960 --> 47:46.952
- Ain't that right, Bravo?
- Yes, Sergeant!

47:47.040 --> 47:48.793
See what I mean, sir? They're killers.

47:48.880 --> 47:50.599
They're having the time of their lives.

47:50.720 --> 47:52.518
So if your company
wants to frack the living shit

47:52.640 --> 47:55.474
out of the Barnett Shale, that's fine,
that's your prerogative,

47:55.600 --> 47:57.080
but don't go doing it on our account.

47:57.160 --> 47:58.958
You got your business, sir, and we got ours.

47:59.040 --> 48:01.999
You just keep on drillin', sir,
and we'll keep on killin'.

48:05.640 --> 48:06.869
Okay.

48:09.280 --> 48:10.714
Okay.

48:11.960 --> 48:13.679
I'm gonna go now.

48:20.080 --> 48:24.120
Yo, Dave, after the Army, man,
you... You really should consider acting.

48:25.000 --> 48:27.913
Dime ain't no act.
He just likes fucking with people.

48:28.000 --> 48:29.639
What do you think acting is, man?

48:30.800 --> 48:34.396
Damn it, Billy, why did I have to
give that nice man such a hard time?

48:34.480 --> 48:36.153
Hard to say, Sergeant.

48:38.360 --> 48:40.511
Maybe I'm just an asshole?

48:41.160 --> 48:42.992
Maybe you are, Sergeant.

48:45.680 --> 48:47.831
Good man, Billy. Stay sharp.

48:53.000 --> 48:54.593
- Hey, Mango.
- Yeah, buddy?

48:54.680 --> 48:56.558
I met somebody at the press conference.

48:56.640 --> 48:59.314
- A cheerleader.
- Don't be an idiot, Billy.

48:59.400 --> 49:02.074
I'm telling you, this girl and I...
We sort of connected.

49:02.160 --> 49:03.560
Actually, we made out.

49:03.640 --> 49:05.950
What? And then you banged her?

49:06.040 --> 49:07.315
Man, this is serious.

49:07.400 --> 49:10.074
I want to see her again,
get to know her better.

49:10.160 --> 49:11.958
I hate to tell you this, Billy,
but you got to go for it

49:12.040 --> 49:13.156
- right now, bro.
- Thanks for your service.

49:13.240 --> 49:15.118
Thank you. 'Cause by the time we get back,

49:15.200 --> 49:17.635
she's gonna be fucking
this big-ass linebacker.

49:17.720 --> 49:20.189
Buddy, she's gonna be like,
"Ay! Ay! Billy who? Ay!"

49:20.280 --> 49:22.556
- Fuck you, asshole.
- I'm just saying,

49:22.640 --> 49:24.438
give her a call, man.

49:25.440 --> 49:27.636
You... You don't have her number, do you?

49:27.720 --> 49:29.677
Billy, Billy, Billy, Billy, Billy.

49:29.760 --> 49:31.433
Hey, what's up, vato?

49:31.520 --> 49:33.398
Yeah, what's up, vato?

49:33.480 --> 49:35.312
- Chillin', chillin'.
- Yeah. My friend Billy here

49:35.400 --> 49:37.790
is feeling a little stress, you know?
Girl troubles.

49:37.880 --> 49:40.634
Hey, Billy. I'm Hector.
I got just the thing for that.

49:40.720 --> 49:43.440
- Let's go outside.
- All right.

49:50.240 --> 49:51.959
What is this place?

49:52.280 --> 49:54.875
Nowhere, man.
One of them place that don't exist.

49:54.960 --> 49:56.917
Good for smoke breaks.

49:58.240 --> 49:59.913
You think we should?

50:00.400 --> 50:02.517
The hell are they gonna do, Billy,

50:02.600 --> 50:04.159
send us to Iraq?

50:08.920 --> 50:11.071
What's that all about?

50:11.160 --> 50:13.720
- Norm's fancy-ass new stadium.
- It's huge.

50:13.800 --> 50:15.871
This team hasn't made
the playoffs in, like, years.

50:15.960 --> 50:17.952
- They suck.
- Doesn't matter.

50:18.040 --> 50:20.760
Some folks pay tens of thousands of dollars.

50:20.840 --> 50:24.231
- For seats?
- Just to reserve the right to buy seats.

50:24.320 --> 50:25.993
Jesus.

50:26.480 --> 50:29.234
Rich people. I don't get 'em.

50:29.320 --> 50:32.199
They don't get you, either, Billy.

50:34.360 --> 50:37.000
Well... Thanks for sharing, my bro.

50:37.080 --> 50:38.560
Appreciate it.

50:38.680 --> 50:40.831
Hey, got to support the troops.

50:40.920 --> 50:42.036
Hooah.

50:42.480 --> 50:44.312
You know, I'm thinking of signing up.

50:45.640 --> 50:47.199
- For real?
